import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby('cluster')[['life_expect', 'fertility']].mean().reset_index()
    melted_data = pd.melt(grouped_data, id_vars='cluster', var_name='metric', value_name='value')
    sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='value', hue='metric', data=melted_data)
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy and fertility rate for each cluster?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
